section.p: The template is used to record information for plapable masses which are detected during the study.

ol.li: SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @classCode="OBS" Observation (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.6 HL7ActClass) (CONF:1096)
SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @moodCode="EVN" Event (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.1001 HL7ActMood) (CONF:1097)

SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] id (CONF:1098)
A sequence number for the observation. [SEND: PMSEQ]

SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] code (CONF:1099), where the @code SHALL be selected from ValueSet Palpable Mass Examination Set locally defined STATIC (CONF:1559)
A value to indicate the particular palpable observation. [SEND: PMTESTCD, PMTEST]

MAY contain zero or one [0..1] statusCode (CONF:1101), where the @code SHALL be selected from (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.14 ActStatus) (CONF:1560)
Used to indicate whether or not a measurement has been performed. [SEND: PMSTAT]

SHOULD contain zero or one [0..1] value (CONF:1102)
The recorded palpable mass finding as up to three observation values, using both original units and a standard format or set of units. The finding may be recorded as a coded value - if the result is character based - or as a physical quantity - if the result is numeric. [SEND: PMORRES, PMORRESU, PMSTRESC, PMSTRESN, PMSTRESU]

SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] entryRelationship (CONF:1103)
Identifies the SDTM or SEND domain the record is assigned to.
Contains @typeCode="REFR" REFR
Contains exactly one [1..1] Domain Assignment (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.30)

SHOULD contain zero or one [0..1] entryRelationship (CONF:1104)
Information on whether a predefined data item was collected, and the timing of collection.
Contains @typeCode="COMP" COMP
Contains exactly one [1..1] Data Collection (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.27)

MAY contain zero or one [0..1] entryRelationship (CONF:1105)
Information on the reason a scheduled activity was not carried out.
Contains @typeCode="COMP" COMP
Contains exactly one [1..1] Non Performance Reason (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.56)

SHOULD contain zero or one [0..1] targetSiteCode (CONF:1106), where the @code SHALL be selected from ValueSet Anatomical Location C74456 STATIC (CONF:1107)
The body site for the palpable mass finding. [SEND: PMLOC]

MAY contain zero or one [0..1] participant (CONF:1108)
Records the role of the person evaluating the finding.
Contains exactly one [1..1] Study Finding Evaluator (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.84)

SHOULD contain zero or one [0..1] participant (CONF:1109)
Records the identifer of a body mass associated with the observation.
Contains exactly one [1..1] Mass Identification (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.51)

SHOULD contain zero or one [0..1] entryRelationship (CONF:1110)
Captures the planned study day for making an observation or recording a finding.
Contains @typeCode="REFR" REFR
Contains exactly one [1..1] Planned Study Day (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.68)

MAY contain zero or more [0..*] entryRelationship (CONF:1111)
Establishes a relationship between this record and another record.
Contains @typeCode="REFR" REFR
Contains exactly one [1..1] Related Record (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.75)

MAY contain zero or more [0..*] entryRelationship (CONF:1112)
Allows the association of a supplemental value - outside of the content specfied for the domain - to the record.
Contains @typeCode="COMP" COMP
Contains exactly one [1..1] Supplemental Value (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.96)

MAY contain zero or more [0..*] entryRelationship (CONF:1113)
A place to insert comments related to a particular finding.
